description: Require meaningful tests when fixing logic in main process or packages
globs: electron/**,packages/**
alwaysApply: false
---

# Tests required (Sonar loop)

When a Sonar fix touches **logic** under `electron/` or `packages/`:

- Add or extend a test in `electron/__tests__/*.test.mjs` (Node `--test`) or `packages/*/test/*.test.ts` (vitest).
- Cover the behavior that regressed or the branch you changed — not trivial "expect(true)".
- Pure UI/style fixes in `app/` do not require new tests unless you extract testable helpers.

Run `pnpm run test:coverage` before opening the PR.
